I said I don't want to do this.

276
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:48,020
-Why not?
-Just because.

277
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:50,150
I'm not doing it.

278
00:22:50,230 --> 00:22:51,820
Why?

279
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:54,200
Why do you not want to do this?

280
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:56,070
You've been doing well
with the counseling.

281
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,910
You need to face this to get better.

282
00:22:57,990 --> 00:23:01,120
Will you keep living as a doctor
who can't operate?

283
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,960
Maybe later.

284
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:06,790
I'll do it some other time.

285
00:23:06,870 --> 00:23:08,130
When would it be?

286
00:23:08,580 --> 00:23:11,050
It's about time
to stop torturing yourself.

287
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,260
-Here.
-Thanks.

288
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:25,890
Now you look like Cha Yu-ri.

289
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:30,020
Yu-ri.

290
00:23:30,650 --> 00:23:31,480
Yes?

291
00:23:31,570 --> 00:23:33,280
For the past five years,

292
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:38,360
were you around me as well?

293
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:42,910
Sure. I stuck around you all the time.

294
00:23:44,540 --> 00:23:48,330
Even I forgot my birthday,
but you remembered it every year.

295
00:23:50,040 --> 00:23:52,840
Maybe I was struggling not to forget you.

296
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:56,220
I guess that's why.

297
00:23:57,930 --> 00:23:59,050
After you left,

298
00:24:00,090 --> 00:24:01,850
it didn't really hit me at first.

299
00:24:02,850 --> 00:24:04,310
When I studied abroad,

300
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:06,810
we didn't see each other for about a year.

301
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:08,940
It was like that.

302
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:12,690
I felt like you were just away
for a little bit.

303
00:24:15,070 --> 00:24:20,070
And once I realized that I would
never be able to see you again,

304
00:24:21,410 --> 00:24:23,330
I couldn't even eat.

305
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:25,660
I just cried my eyes out.

306
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:29,670
But after a little while,

307
00:24:30,620 --> 00:24:32,420
I felt hungry again.

308
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:36,010
So I started to eat,

309
00:24:36,380 --> 00:24:37,970
take care of Ha-jun,

310
00:24:38,090 --> 00:24:39,180
and work.

311
00:24:43,140 --> 00:24:44,430
And one day,

312
00:24:47,730 --> 00:24:48,810
I realized that

313
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,400
I was forgetting about you.

314
00:24:54,110 --> 00:24:55,690
I just celebrated your birthdays

315
00:24:56,690 --> 00:24:58,570
because I wanted to cling on to you.

316
00:24:59,610 --> 00:25:01,320
Because I was sorry for you.

317
00:25:04,530 --> 00:25:05,870
And you knew it, right?

318
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:07,910
Of course, I did.

319
00:25:08,540 --> 00:25:11,290
Actually I was sad
that you were forgetting about me.

320
00:25:13,540 --> 00:25:14,540
But

321
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:20,090
I was afraid if I wouldn't be forgotten.

322
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:26,260
Watching people
have hard times because of me,

323
00:25:27,310 --> 00:25:29,100
was real hell.

324
00:25:30,810 --> 00:25:31,640
Gang-hwa?

325
00:25:36,190 --> 00:25:37,780
So you knew it too.

326
00:25:38,860 --> 00:25:40,320
That Gang-hwa has a problem.

327
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,740
I do. I was around him all the time.

328
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:47,330
He recently received a probation.

329
00:25:47,410 --> 00:25:49,080
I found out about it later on though.

330
00:25:52,830 --> 00:25:54,710
That's what I did to him.

331
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,210
I broke his heart.

332
00:25:57,290 --> 00:25:59,090
It's not your fault.

333
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:01,510
Isn't it like you died
because you wanted to.

334
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:04,890
But it was my choice.

335
00:26:07,430 --> 00:26:09,850
I just made him feel guilty.

336
00:26:29,330 --> 00:26:32,410
Where did she go leaving me alone?

337
00:26:35,330 --> 00:26:36,330
Oh, right.

338
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:38,920
That's right.

339
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:47,260
SUPERNATURAL POWERS
SHAMAN MS. MI-DONG

340
00:26:47,850 --> 00:26:50,640
SEO BONG-YEON

341
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:06,320
I know you're a stone-hearted human,

342
00:27:06,910 --> 00:27:11,240
but how could you send them up
just like that?

343
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:12,790
My point.

344
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,290
I didn't even get to say goodbye. Damn it.

345
00:27:21,050 --> 00:27:22,590
You guys are not human.

346
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:25,880
To Guk-bong...

347
00:27:26,550 --> 00:27:28,180
I mean, to people,

348
00:27:28,430 --> 00:27:30,800
you guys are just demons
who should be sent up.

349
00:27:30,890 --> 00:27:32,600
How could you say something so harsh?

350
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:33,890
I know.

351
00:27:33,970 --> 00:27:36,890
So if you don't want to get caught
and sent up all of a sudden like them,

352
00:27:37,100 --> 00:27:38,850
stop avoiding Guk-bong

353
00:27:39,230 --> 00:27:43,360
and get over your regrets in this world.

354
00:27:46,950 --> 00:27:48,360
This is really frustrating.

355
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:57,160
Hello?

356
00:27:57,250 --> 00:27:58,540
Hello, ma'am.

357
00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:00,790
Do you make domiciliary visits?

358
00:28:01,130 --> 00:28:02,130
What?

359
00:28:08,180 --> 00:28:10,720
Min-jeong. Believe it or not,

360
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:12,600
it's true.

361
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,450
What are you doing?

362
00:28:32,410 --> 00:28:33,580
Get off, Yu-ri.

363
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:37,830
You said we'd hang out at my place.

364
00:28:38,410 --> 00:28:39,920
We will drink. So I can't drive.

365
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,000
Let's walk.

366
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:47,300
I'm hungry. Let's go.

367
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,600
-I'm so hungry.
-Me too.

368
00:29:02,690 --> 00:29:04,690
-I shouted too much.
-I know.

369
00:29:04,770 --> 00:29:07,740
I couldn't help it
because you drove so fast.

370
00:29:18,580 --> 00:29:19,580
-Is it here?
-Yes.

371
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:20,660
It's for us.

372
00:29:20,830 --> 00:29:22,620
-It just came right on time.
-I know.

373
00:29:23,460 --> 00:29:24,710
-Please enjoy.
-Thank you.

374
00:29:24,790 --> 00:29:26,300
It's pork belly meat.

375
00:29:26,380 --> 00:29:28,800
-Let's go.
-Mom, Yu-ri and Hyeon-jeong are here.

376
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:31,050
Gosh, I can't wait.

377
00:29:31,260 --> 00:29:34,640
-Let's eat.
-It must be really good.

378
00:29:35,890 --> 00:29:37,430
Hello, Ms. Jeon.

379
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:50,280
CHA MU-PUNG, JEON EUN-SUK,
CHA YU-RI, CHA YEON-JI

380
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,150
-It looks delicious.
-It's warm.

381
00:30:30,230 --> 00:30:31,240
My goodness.

382
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:33,400
-I'm hungry.
-It looks great.

383
00:30:33,490 --> 00:30:36,370
Here's a cold beer for you.

384
00:30:36,450 --> 00:30:38,200
Yeon-ji, you're the best.

385
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:39,740
We have five drinkers here.

386
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:41,660
This is far from enough.

387
00:30:41,830 --> 00:30:43,540
I don't drink beer.

388
00:30:43,620 --> 00:30:44,580
I like soju.

389
00:30:44,790 --> 00:30:48,040
I knew it. You're so my type.

390
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,800
Mom, I'll get you soju.

391
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:52,170
Here, Dad.

392
00:30:52,260 --> 00:30:53,590
-My daughter is the best.
-Gosh.

393
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:54,720
It's good, isn't it?

394
00:30:55,970 --> 00:30:58,350
-This is nice.
-Dad, please open this for me.

395
00:30:58,430 --> 00:30:59,810
Give me that.

396
00:30:59,890 --> 00:31:01,350
All right.

397
00:31:03,310 --> 00:31:04,520
It's open.

398
00:31:05,190 --> 00:31:07,400
It flew away like this.

399
00:31:07,980 --> 00:31:09,400
Let's drink.

400
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:11,480
Here. Have some of this.

401
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:13,280
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

402
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:15,240
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

403
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:20,740
It tastes so good.

404
00:31:23,750 --> 00:31:26,920
So we're all together with Hyeon-jeong.

405
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,790
It's been so long since we did this.

406
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,040
I know.

407
00:31:30,130 --> 00:31:32,960
I've been too busy
working and raising my kid.

408
00:31:33,460 --> 00:31:35,840
She was just afraid
she would remind us of Yu-ri,

409
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:37,890
so she was being thoughtful.

410
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:40,350
Do you think I don't know that?

411
00:31:42,470 --> 00:31:44,060
I had no idea

412
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:47,770
this day would come again.

413
00:31:47,850 --> 00:31:50,110
What are you doing, Dad? This isn't right.

414
00:31:50,190 --> 00:31:53,480
She's right. Why are you being so silly?

415
00:31:53,570 --> 00:31:54,860
Okay. I get it.

416
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:56,780
-I'm done. It's over.
-It's over.

417
00:31:57,110 --> 00:31:59,950
-Mr. Cha, please stop.
-What's over?

418
00:32:00,030 --> 00:32:02,870
It's nothing.
Your dad is just being silly again.

419
00:32:02,950 --> 00:32:04,910
Do you say things like that?

420
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,080
Sure.

421
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:07,290
She says all kinds of stuff.

422
00:32:07,370 --> 00:32:09,420
-Gosh, Dad.
-Stop it.

423
00:32:11,590 --> 00:32:13,130
-It tastes good.
-So

424
00:32:13,670 --> 00:32:15,090
did you guys have fun?

425
00:32:15,170 --> 00:32:16,420
Yes. We had a lot of fun.

426
00:32:16,510 --> 00:32:19,800
Hyeon-jeong's driving has improved a lot.
She was too afraid to run at 50km before.

427
00:32:19,890 --> 00:32:21,180
Hey, that was a long time ago.

428
00:32:21,260 --> 00:32:25,180
That's not true.
I was a novice driver back then.

429
00:32:25,270 --> 00:32:27,600
Still, 50km is too slow.

430
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:30,480
Here, Yu-ri. Try this.

431
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:32,810
You seem to have only one daughter.

432
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:35,150
You're my son. All right.

433
00:32:35,230 --> 00:32:37,990
I didn't know I was a son.

434
00:32:38,070 --> 00:32:41,780
All right. I should give this to my son.

435
00:32:41,870 --> 00:32:44,120
Here. Good.

436
00:32:44,410 --> 00:32:45,950
Why don't we take a picture together?

437
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:47,660
-Good.
-Let's do that.

438
00:32:47,750 --> 00:32:49,160
Do I look okay?

439
00:32:49,250 --> 00:32:51,000
-You look perfect.
-You look beautiful.

440
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:52,830
-Don't worry.
-You're always pretty.

441
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:53,840
I'll put this on here.

442
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:56,130
Gather together and look at the camera.

443
00:32:56,210 --> 00:32:57,510
Mr. Cha, come closer.

444
00:32:57,590 --> 00:32:59,130
One...

445
00:32:59,470 --> 00:33:00,800
Come closer to each other.

446
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:03,470
-One...
-Is it how it works?

447
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:06,850
Let me see the picture.

448
00:33:06,930 --> 00:33:08,930
I'll show you.

449
00:35:08,470 --> 00:35:11,560
I'm very grateful to Hyeon-jeong.

450
00:35:13,180 --> 00:35:15,230
I'm always grateful to her.

451
00:35:15,730 --> 00:35:17,190
Did you like it, Yu-ri?

452
00:35:17,810 --> 00:35:19,520
Yes. I loved it.

453
00:35:21,190 --> 00:35:23,070
What was so good?

454
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:27,030
I liked the wind,

455
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:28,570
I liked the air,

456
00:35:28,780 --> 00:35:30,580
and I liked Hyeon-jeong next to me.

457
00:35:31,950 --> 00:35:33,330
I'm glad to hear that.

458
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:37,210
Things will be always like that
from now on.

459
00:35:38,250 --> 00:35:41,290
We will have happy moments
like that every day, Yu-ri.

460
00:35:46,050 --> 00:35:47,180
Do you not want it?

461
00:35:47,970 --> 00:35:49,550
Of course, I want it.

462
00:35:52,930 --> 00:35:54,020
What?

463
00:35:55,890 --> 00:35:57,100
Dad.

464
00:35:57,810 --> 00:35:58,770
Is Dad sleeping already?

465
00:35:59,770 --> 00:36:03,400
Dad, you can't sleep here.

466
00:36:04,230 --> 00:36:06,740
-My gosh.
-It's been less than a minute.

467
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:09,990
It was somewhere around here. Where is it?

468
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:12,830
There it is. It says Misaeng.

469
00:36:15,580 --> 00:36:18,040
What is he doing here?

470
00:36:21,420 --> 00:36:22,420
Hey.

471
00:36:25,340 --> 00:36:26,670
Gosh, it hurts.

472
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:28,300
-It hurts.
-What are you doing here?

473
00:36:28,380 --> 00:36:29,930
Gosh, it's not like that.

474
00:36:30,010 --> 00:36:31,140
Let go of me.

475
00:36:31,220 --> 00:36:32,930
-It really hurts.
-Come here.

476
00:36:35,350 --> 00:36:38,230
Come here. I got you.

477
00:36:38,730 --> 00:36:40,940
-Just follow me.
-It hurts.

478
00:36:41,020 --> 00:36:42,270
Hello.

479
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:45,440
Stay still. Stop.

480
00:36:45,530 --> 00:36:47,940
What's with your arms?

481
00:36:49,150 --> 00:36:50,280
Is something there?

482
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:52,660
What have you been up to these days?

483
00:36:52,950 --> 00:36:54,620
Why is there a ghost around you?

484
00:36:54,780 --> 00:36:56,330
What? A ghost?

485
00:36:56,410 --> 00:36:57,830
-Stay still.
-Ghost?

486
00:36:57,910 --> 00:36:59,750
I told you to stand still!

487
00:36:59,830 --> 00:37:00,960
Isn't it staying still?

488
00:37:01,540 --> 00:37:03,750
-It hurts.
-Stop it. Stay still.

489
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:13,050
Is he always so stupid like that?

490
00:37:15,060 --> 00:37:16,310
Because she's not here.

491
00:37:17,020 --> 00:37:17,970
Who?

492
00:37:18,310 --> 00:37:19,270
His wife.

493
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:20,600
He's Hyeon-jeong's boy.

494
00:37:20,690 --> 00:37:22,690
Hyeon-jeong. Where are you?

495
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:27,110
Hurry and come right away, Hyeon-jeong.

496
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:31,610
Gosh, you now know Yu-ri was around you
for five years.

497
00:37:31,700 --> 00:37:33,240
Just come over here.

498
00:37:34,660 --> 00:37:36,870
I didn't know about it.

499
00:37:37,830 --> 00:37:38,870
Are you sure

500
00:37:39,660 --> 00:37:40,870
there's a ghost next to you?

501
00:37:41,750 --> 00:37:44,330
Why? Why is it doing this to me?

502
00:37:44,710 --> 00:37:46,840
Is it because I refused
to write a fake diagnosis?

503
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:49,510
Gosh, it's no big deal.

504
00:37:52,180 --> 00:37:54,680
"Gosh, it's no big deal."

505
00:37:56,640 --> 00:37:57,470
Then why?

506
00:37:58,390 --> 00:37:59,850
Why are you hanging around with him?

507
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,850
Right. That one.

508
00:38:01,940 --> 00:38:03,060
There's something

509
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:06,150
only he can do for me.

510
00:38:08,730 --> 00:38:09,940
What?

511
00:38:12,070 --> 00:38:13,700
What is it?

512
00:38:14,070 --> 00:38:16,570
Ms. Mi-dong, please tell me what he says.

513
00:38:16,660 --> 00:38:18,080
Why? Why is he doing this to me?

514
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:21,660
So there's something
only you can do for him.

515
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:24,250
What is it?

516
00:38:28,550 --> 00:38:30,170
Please tell my mom

517
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:31,970
that I didn't

518
00:38:33,970 --> 00:38:35,090
kill myself.

519
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:42,850
He knows that it wasn't a suicide.

520
00:38:44,100 --> 00:38:46,270
What does he say?

521
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:48,820
What is it? What?

522
00:38:49,690 --> 00:38:51,900
Ms. Mi-dong, please.
I need a simultaneous interpretation.

523
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:53,900
I can't wait.

524
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:56,570
I'm very anxious.

525
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:28,150
It must've been fun

526
00:39:31,820 --> 00:39:36,820
to see how much I loved her
like some kind of an idiot.

527
00:39:44,250 --> 00:39:46,120
No, it wasn't like that.

528
00:39:48,790 --> 00:39:50,540
Do you know what I said?

529
00:39:53,340 --> 00:39:55,880
I said I'm curious about her
because she looks like Seo-woo's mom.

530
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,140
That I'm envious

531
00:40:00,350 --> 00:40:01,970
because she looks like Seo-woo.

532
00:40:04,430 --> 00:40:05,640
I had no idea.

533
00:40:07,770 --> 00:40:09,150
I was like a fool.

534
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:24,370
You should've told me first.

535
00:40:30,250 --> 00:40:32,090
That's what you should've done.

536
00:40:42,390 --> 00:40:44,600
It has been a while

537
00:40:47,180 --> 00:40:48,850
since you looked so happy

538
00:40:51,270 --> 00:40:53,820
when you were around other people.

539
00:40:57,110 --> 00:40:58,320
I was afraid

540
00:41:00,570 --> 00:41:01,950
you would get hurt.

541
00:41:10,500 --> 00:41:11,620
I'm sorry.

542
00:41:22,970 --> 00:41:24,850
Before caring about my happiness,

543
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:28,730
you should care about yours.

544
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:32,730
Before seeing my wound,

545
00:41:33,230 --> 00:41:35,230
you should take care of yours first.

546
00:41:39,240 --> 00:41:41,150
